Families, the deadline to submit your application for Free and Reduced-Priced Meals (FARM) is September 29! Be sure to get your application in today!All families can apply to Free-and-Reduced Price Meals vía your Infinite Campus Parent Portal under “more” and then by clicking “meal benefits”. Or visit: www.elhaynes.org/nutrition

Familias, la fecha límite para presentar su solicitud de Comidas Gratuitas y de Precio Reducido (FARM, por sus siglas en inglés) es el 29 de septiembre! ¡Asegúrese de recibir su aplicación hoy mismo! Todas las familias pueden aplicar a comidas de precio libre y reducido vía su Portal para Padres del "Infinite Campus"more(más)" y luego haciendo clic en "meal benefits(beneficios de comida)". O visite: www.elhaynes.org/nutrition

The pandemic has changed our way of life and as a result, many of us may be feeling isolated, anxious, bored, frustrated, stressed, and many other emotions. post_text:
At an Independence Day celebration on July 5, 1852, Frederick Douglass gave his now-famous keynote address: What to a Slave is the Fourth of July? Today, we reflect on his words and the current duality of America. We honor those who continue to push for change and progress as we challenge systemic racism and inequity, and we also give thanks to those who have fought for our nation. Freedom will only be achieved when we are all free.

"your denunciation of tyrants brass fronted impudence; your shout of liberty and equality, hollow mockery; your prayers and hymns, your sermons and thanks-givings, with all your religious parade and solemnity, are to him, mere bombast, fraud, deception, impiety, and hypocrisy -- a thin veil to cover up crimes which would disgrace a nation of savages. There is not a nation on the earth guilty of practices more shocking and bloody than are the people of the United States, at this very hour."

E.L. Haynes stands in solidarity with our students, families, and colleagues in speaking out against the conditions of systemic oppression and racism that continue to threaten Black lives and humanity.

We believe that education is a critical tool in breaking down systems of oppression. We are committed to dismantling these systems, and together creating a more just and kind world.

She creates experiences that students will always remember; experiences that will serve as shining memories for her students for years to come.” - Brittany Wagner-Friel, Principal, E.L. Families! Since we will facilitate home learning for a longer period of time, we want to survey families on what their technology capacity is at home. Our Wellness Program includes multiple supports for our students. When we opened in 2004, our founders had a vision for a school that provided comprehensive wrap-around supports for our students and families.
